a-cranberry-hibiscus-sabdariffa", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Central/West Africa, widely grown in tropical India", "traits": "Shrubby annual/perennial (2-2.5m tall in Kerala climate), lobed leaves, yellow flowers with red center, bright red calyces", "flesh_fruit": "Red fleshy calyces, very tart/tangy flavor similar to cranberry, rich in vitamin C and anthocyanins", "yield_notes": "Abundant production, multiple harvests during monsoon season", "growing_notes": "PERFECT FOR KERALA TROPICAL MONSOON CLIMATE. Thrives in heat, humidity, and monsoon rains. Traditional crop in Kerala - widely grown for ''gongura'' leaves and calyces. Calyces used exactly like cranberries - chutneys, pickles, drinks, preserves. Leaves used in curries, rice dishes (pulihora). Heat-loving (grows best 25-35°C). Plant after monsoon begins. Highly productive in Kerala conditions. Called ''Indian Sorrel'' or ''Gongura''. Non-GMO, open-pollinated.", "availability": "Widely available - Kerala nurseries, agricultural stores, local markets (Thiruvalla, Pathanamthitta, Kottayam), seed suppliers across India", "sort_order": 0}, {"name": "Roselle - Green Calyx Variety", "slug": "roselle-green-calyx-variety", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Selected Indian variety", "traits": "Green calyces instead of red, same plant growth", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 1}, {"name": "Cranberry Hibiscus (Hibiscus acetosella)", "slug": "cranberry-hibiscus-hibiscus-acetosella", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Africa, tropical regions", "traits": "Deep red/maroon leaves, 1-2m tall, ornamental and edible", "flesh_fruit": "Edible leaves (tangy flavor), used fresh or cooked", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "EXCELLENT FOR KERALA. Thrives in monsoon humidity and heat. Grown for edible ornamental leaves, not fruit.