t, concentrated tartness", "yield_notes": "Heavy seasonal production", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 9}, {"name": "Rambuttan (Nephelium lappaceum)", "slug": "rambuttan-nephelium-lappaceum", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Southeast Asia, successfully cultivated Kerala (Pathanamthitta district)", "traits": "Medium tree (12-20m), hairy red fruits in clusters", "flesh_fruit": "White translucent flesh, sweet with slight tartness, grape-like texture", "yield_notes": "Seasonal fruiting May-August (monsoon)", "growing_notes": "SUCCESSFULLY NATURALIZED IN KERALA, especially Pathanamthitta district (very near Thiruvalla). Thrives in monsoon climate. Sweet-tart flavor. Commercially cultivated. Related to lychee. Productive in tropical conditions.", "availability": "Kerala nurseries (particularly Pathanamthitta district nurseries, very local to Thiruvalla area)", "sort_order": 10}, {"name": "Mangoosteen (Garcinia mangostana)", "slug": "mangoosteen-garcinia-mangostana", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Southeast Asia, cultivated Kerala", "traits": "Evergreen tree (10-25m), purple round fruits", "flesh_fruit": "White segmented flesh, slightly sweet-tart, aromatic", "yield_notes": "Seasonal fruiting", "growing_notes": "Grown in Kerala (Pathanamthitta, Ernakulam). Thrives in tropical monsoon. ''Queen of fruits''. Sweet with slight tartness. High-value exotic fruit in Kerala.", "availability": "Specialty Kerala nurseries, exotic fruit growers Pathanamthitta/Idukki", "sort_order": 11}], "variety_count": 17}'::jsonb,
