k when fully ripe", "yield_notes": "High, abundant juice and vesicles", "growing_notes": "CSIRO-bred hybrid suitable for Brisbane subtropical climate. Ideal for dishes requiring lime juice. Striking red aromatic acid fruit. Compact growth perfect for containers. Rare and difficult to find. Grafted onto standard citrus rootstock.", "availability": "Gondwana Native Limes NSW (only licensed propagator in NSW), One Green World USA, Forest + Field, limited availability", "sort_order": 26}, {"name": "Australian Sunrise", "slug": "australian-sunrise", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "CSIRO (Faustrimedin hybrid seedling selection)", "traits": "Cross: Calamondin (mandarin × kumquat) × Finger Lime", "flesh_fruit": "Pear-shaped orange fruit, makes excellent marmalade", "yield_notes": "Good", "growing_notes": "CSIRO-bred hybrid. Good for Brisbane subtropical climate. Unique pear shape. Excellent for preserves.", "availability": "Specialist citrus nurseries", "sort_order": 27}, {"name": "General Grafted Finger Lime", "slug": "general-grafted-finger-lime", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Australian varieties grafted, available in India (2020s introduction)", "traits": "Grafted on evergreen rootstock for Kerala conditions, 1-2m height potential", "flesh_fruit": "Caviar-like lime pearls, variable colors (green/yellow/pink), minty citrus-forward aroma, tangy sweet slightly sour flavor", "yield_notes": "Fruits 1-2 years after grafting", "growing_notes": "Adapts to Kerala tropical monsoon climate (15-40°C ideal range). Requires well-drained soil with pH 5.5-6.5. Plant in full sun to partial shade with monsoon protection. Water regularly during dry periods. Tolerates Kerala''s warm humid conditions. Protect from strong monsoon winds. Can grow in containers. Fertilize: 20kg FYM, 100g urea, 1kg superphosphate per year for young plants.", "availability": "Greens of Kerala (Kochi), Veliyath Gardens (